$ Microsoft Power Platform

Microsoft Power Platform comprises four products
  • → Microsoft/products/Power/BI
  • → Microsoft/products/Power/Apps
  • → Microsoft/products/Power/Automate Power Automate (formerly known as *Microsoft Flow*)
  • Power Virtual Agents


? These four products are built upon
    • Common Data Service
    • Connectors & Gateways

PowerPlatforms also has has two add-ons
  • AI Builder
  • Power Apps portals


{ Microsoft Dataverse (formerly Common Data Service) #ms-dataverse

  → Microsoft/products/Power/Platform/Dataverse[Microsoft Dataverse] is the backbone that powers → Microsoft/Dynamics[Dynamics] 365 and Power Platform. It is a 
  language witw which the meaning of → development/Data can be shared accross applications.


? DataVerse also available to → Microsoft/Azure/products/Data-Lake-Storage with «Common Data Model folders».


? There are two → development/web/service[web services] that allow to work with → development/Data and → development/Data/metadata in Common Data Service:
    • Common Data Service Web API
    • → https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/powerapps/developer/common-data-service/org-service/overview[Common Data Service Organization Service] (which seems to revolve around the → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/Microsoft/Xrm/Sdk/IOrganizationService[`IOrganizationService`] interface.



}

